A foetus
was found on Tuesday afternoon in a rubbish bin along Queen Street, in the Durban
CBD, in kwaZulu Natal. ER24's
Spokesperson Russel Meiring said paramedics arrived on the scene at 12h00,
after they were called by the local authorities. "Upon
arrival, paramedics found the local authorities gathered around a refuse
bin," Meiring said. According
to Meiring on further inspection, paramedics found a male foetus wrapped in a
plastic bag. "Unfortunately,
nothing more could be done by paramedics," Meiring said. The
local authorities were on the scene for further investigations.